    "summary": "This paper studies few-layer (Bi0.16Sb0.84)2Te3 topological-insulator films using multi-tip STM/STS and nanoscale four-point transport to test whether spectroscopic edge states are truly ballistic quantum spin Hall (QSH) edge channels. The key result is that edge-localized LDOS is observed at step edges, but transport measurements and finite-element/analytical modeling show no ballistic edge conductance for 2 QL and 3 QL films, implying the observed edge states are trivial rather than topological.",
